ATTACHMENT A
Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 Meadow Lake Wind Farm III LLC Reactive Power Compensation May 25, 2018
MEADOW LAKE WIND FARM III LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Meadow Lake Wind Farm II LLC ("Meadow Lake III") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Meadow Lake III generating facility ("Meadow Lake III Facility").
The Meadow Lake III Facility is a wind turbine generating facility located in White County, Indiana. The Meadow Lake III Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Indiana Michigan Power Company and under the operational control of the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Meadow Lake III's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Meadow Lake III Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Meadow Lake III's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Meadow Lake III shall be subject to Schedule 2 of PJM's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $376,363.64 The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $31,363.63
